<main class="page-main">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About Tipi Raisers</h1>
      <p>A community-driven initiative building homes, careers, and futures on the reservation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container content-narrow">
      <h2>Our Story</h2>
      <!-- TODO: Replace with your organization's full origin story -->
      <p>Tipi Raisers was born from years of watching our community struggle with housing that didn't reflect the dignity and strength of our people. With backgrounds in construction, community organizing, and tribal advocacy, our founding team came together with a singular mission: to build quality, affordable homes on the reservation — with our own hands, our own workers, and our own vision.</p>
      <p>We've been working in the trenches of home construction and community development for over a decade. The Reservation Homes Project is the formalization of that work — a structured, funded, and determined effort to solve the housing crisis in our community once and for all.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-pad bg-earth">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title text-center">Our Mission</h2>
      <div class="mission-pillars">
        <div class="mission-item">
          <div class="mission-num">01</div>
          <h3>Affordable Housing</h3>
          <p>Provide quality, affordable homes to tribal members who have been underserved by existing housing programs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mission-item">
          <div class="mission-num">02</div>
          <h3>Indigenous Employment</h3>
          <p>Create sustainable income and career pathways for Indigenous community members through the construction industry.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mission-item">
          <div class="mission-num">03</div>
          <h3>Generational Skills</h3>
          <p>Train the next generation of construction professionals on the reservation, keeping expertise and opportunity local.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

