        <div class="team-card">
          <div class="team-photo team-photo-placeholder"></div>
          <h3>Caddis Shook</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Co-Founder/Community Relations</p>
          <p class="team-bio">My reason for working on this cause is because this is such a unique opportunity for a cause and community I have spent and dedicated my life to connecting with and I get to rope that into my school life and community. I think this opportunity alone of working on the house with my peers and faculty of Dawson is such a bonding experience that’s so special to experience. Also, being of service to others is one of the best experiences that I have in my life and cannot wait to continue that with Tipi Raisers and the students I am working with.</p>
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline btn-sm bio-toggle">Read more</button>
        </div>
        <div class="team-card">
          <div class="team-photo team-photo-placeholder"></div>
          <h3>Audrey Moulton</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Co-Founder/Communications and Outreach</p>
          <p class="team-bio">Hi everyone, my name is Audrey Moulton, and I am so excited to be working on this amazing project! I have been passionate about serving others since I was younger, and I am so happy to be able to do this now, working with my school and friends. In addition to the service this provides to native communities in need, this project also gives the students who work on it valuable life skills such as project management, carpentry, and communication, which I am so excited to be learning. Service work makes me feel extremely fulfilled, and I am so grateful for the opportunity I have and the privilege to be able to serve in this way.</p>
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline btn-sm bio-toggle">Read more</button>
        </div>
        <div class="team-card">
          <img src="images/Team/Asher.jpg" alt="Asher Greer" class="team-photo" />
          <h3>Asher Greer</h3>
          <p class="team-role">Co-Founder/Technical Lead</p>
          <p class="team-bio">Being part of this project means having the opportunity to contribute to something that creates a real impact in people’s lives. Supporting communities in need and working toward a cause greater than ourselves makes this experience especially meaningful. It’s something I don’t take for granted, and it motivates me to put my full effort into the work we’re doing.

Working alongside my peers and faculty makes the experience even more powerful. The connections we build and the shared purpose we have throughout the process turn this into more than just a project. It’s about coming together to make a difference, and I’m grateful to be a part of something that has a positive and lasting impact.</p>
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline btn-sm bio-toggle">Read more</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
